values: Wow I havent thought of this site in such a long time, but for some reason i did tonight. I'm thinking i might actually start this up again. Reading my old entries was fun and of course i have changed alot since then. One thing that hasnt changed is my ability to type the least i can but I'm gonna try working on that. I'm almost constantly feeling melancholy lately, especially when i think of her. We talked for such a long time and just when i thought things would change, they have gone pretty much back to what they were before. I'm not satisfied yet and I really wish i could finally rid myself of these feelings but I've tried and its just not possible right now. I really wish i was in the city right now, on those hardwood floors at bridge that changed my life last summer, riding the subway to Chelsea everynight to see the beautiful girls at Parson's and the Ailey program and walking around with E and Laura or jamming in the sweatbox at Fazil's. Things just get worse and worse here and I dont know if i can last another year. Of course i will but things need to change. She needs to change, my father needs to change, my whole situation is draining me day by day and without school to distract me i feel it more everyday. NY took all of those problems away last time and gave me something to look forward too and hope and faith in my future but I am all out of inspiration. I havent been practicing, I havent had a lesson in God knows how long and as much as i want to practice i just cant. I'll just sit there, looking at my case and hitting myself in the head for bieng so stupid. I'm tired of bieng independant. I never wanted to be and now as my mom goes farther and farther away, this constant longing makes itself more noticible in my head and its fucking everything up.

i have no feelings, no reaction, no soul, no compassion. i keep asking myself not why did this happen to me. My family. but why have i not broken down and started crying, broken things, any form of releasing my emotions that never existed in the first place. I once cried because my great aunt died. i never "met" her, she could not even talk, eat, or function. but yet i still cried when i got the news. my great grandmother did not even express as much emotion as me. maybe thats why. have i wasted it? no. it must have been fake. what is wrong with me. the answer is simple. me. i am what is wrong with me. me is what is wrong with i. it doesnt take a psychologist to think logically yet she listens to their echos everytime. and him, the whole world is against him. his own offspring. bullshit i say. caring is not love, love is not caring, if they were the same then they would not be 2 different words. love is an excuse, a way to get out of it. caring is the hard way, as sad as it may be, it is material. dont tell me u love me. dont tell me u care about me. im not stupid, i can think for myself. im not brainwashed. i can see the truth. i have not betrayed u, nature has betrayed us all. not just me, o sorry, i mean you. i remember when i was happy. no, i mean happy. not the fakeness u see everyday, the happy i expressed on the beach, swimming as if a rip tide could never carry me away. but it did didnt it. it carried us all away. and now the result is me. stuck in the middle, stranded on an island with no emotion.

So the clipse, Black eyed peas, N.E.R.D show was amazing. Not only did eric and i get in free and a good view, but i got to hang out on spymob's tour bus. i think i left the 9:30 around 3:10 or sumthin and slept until about 2 this morning. Goin to see them again on the 23rd at AU with Blayne and maybe eric and lizzie. this has definitly been the best month of my life thus far.

o yeah. did my show at the smithsonian museum for american history. That was fun cause we danced with a really good jazz band. then went to my second show that day which was pretty bad. and then sunday....yeah, to many things happened for me to type so im not gonna try.

Props up to ray ray for finding me my new icon...ive been lookin for a drum related pic forever.

I performed with the orchestra on sun at Lincoln theater and it was sooo funny. First, the guest speaker as usual couldnt pronounce maetro kaniyama's name so when the concert master came out to tune us...i looked at him and we both started to crack up. Then in the last piece...every time there was a long marimba solo, some guy in the audience would moan because he had a mental problem or something. Normally, this would not effect me at all, but this really stupid kid behind me started laughing a little loud, which was not really cool, But since it was a distraction...people (including me)started to chuckle a little. It was so hard to hold it in and i almost peed myself. When i looked up at kaniyama, expecting him to be ashamed, he was chuckling a little too! It was so funny, i couldnt breathe and it was seriously the hardest test of self control i have ever been through.

On a fun trip to chuck levine's after orchestra AND tap comp. rehearsal, i met a dude named havi. Man is he awesome!!! not only does he play violin and said he could sell me his old but nice and originally expensive electric violin, but he also is starting a latin/rock/hip-hop/jazz/go-go band! This guy is just like me except hispanic! then i bought a pair of drum sticks. no more waiting for Yoni to finish with his drumsticks so i can have them for myself! 

Oh yeah, while at orchestra today, i get on to the stage and Mr. Samandari tells me to sit principle (first chair of the 2nd violins) Not to be cocky, but usually this would not be a big deal, BUUUUTTT i just moved up into the orchestra so its kinda weird seeing as there are people that have been there longer than me and might be better than me. What is funny is that my teacher expects me to be sitting there. (is it her, or do i just have a lack of confidence) anyway, we had this guest xylophone player from the national symphony orchestra to play rhapsody in blue for the concert and she was amazing!! she was holding two sticks in hand and was just jumping around this huge xylophone. When we finished with her, we got a break so i went into the cafeteria. Mr. Samandari comes up to me saying that he and Mr. Maclain (this grumpy old conductor that has been there forever) had talked about me sitting as principle earlier and that they wanted me to keep the seat. WTF! i dont think that i am that good! i just hope the other people in 2nd dont hate me. 

Holy schnykees, that was the longest post that i have ever written!!

I would like to start off by saying I WILL NEVER GO SNOWBOARDING AGAIN!!!!! (because i hurt the crap out of myself and cannot play violin for the time being.)
Anyway...Staying at Yoni's house for the week has been fun and i hope he doesnt hate me now...haha. Important notice...MR. YOUNG COMES BACK IN A DAY OR 2!!!! cannot wait for my favorite, most pretentious teacher to come back!! I'm not saying that the sub, Joe from 33west was bad... he was just not Mr.Young. Now i will commence writing the english paper on LOTFQ that was due a week or two ago.

What a great day!!!!!!!!! It was just so damn nice outside that i had to go biking with the yonsta to lake kneedwood or whatever its called. jammed as usual and then played some good ole n64. 
After the next 2 weeks i predict that yoni and i will be worst enemies (im stayin at his place for a week). We both agree on this prediction. But seriously, We could get soooo much work done....its gonna be AWESOME!

making

 During my tenure, Houston replaced Los Angeles as the most
smog-ridden

the

American
 history.

 With the help of my brother, the governor of Florida, and my
father's
 appointments to the Supreme Court, I became president after losing
by
 over 500,000 votes.

 ACCOMPLISHMENTS AS PRESIDENT:

 criminal
 record.

one
 billion dollars per week.

period.

the
 U.S. stock market.

 In my first year in office, over 2 million Americans lost their

 and
 that trend continues every month.

 I'm proud that the members of my cabinet are the richest of any

 Rice, has a Chevron oil tanker named after her.

 I set the record for most campaign fundraising trips by a U.S.

 I am the all-time U.S. and world record-holder for receiving the
most
 corporate campaign donations.

 My largest lifetime campaign contributor, and one of my best
friends,

in
 U.S. History, Enron. My political party used Enron private jets and

Court
 during my election decision.

 I have protected my friends at Enron and Halliburton against

 to

 I've broken more international treaties than any President in U.S.

 I am the first President in U.S. history to have the United Nations

 I withdrew the U.S. from the World Court of Law.--actually what
 happened
 is the World Court is changing into the International Criminal

 to having the US have charges brought up against them, they have

laws
 within the ICC, but not have those laws applied to our country.

 I refused to allow inspectors access to U.S. "prisoners of war"

of
 mankind.

 I am the first President in U.S. history to order an unprovoked,

nation. I

What really has me gone is the fact that I can have feelings for someone I only know a few facts about. It freaks me out that i wish and wish we could have something but i know it could never happen, but maybe it could. Maybe if i let them know im interested in them i could learn more about them and let them know something about me and in doing so, bring us closer together. But before that happens, in comes the fear of embarrassment and rejection, So im caught between two (what i feel are) predicaments. Should i take the risk? If i dont nothing will happen and i will never know what could have happened if i had. Basically, i need to let my walls down and take some risks even though they may seem small to other people
